serves: 6
---
- 2 tablespoon oil
- 3 teaspoon coriander seeds
- 1 teaspoon cumin seeds
- 30 unit dry curry leaves
- 1 white onion
- 6 clove garlic
- 15 g fresh ginger
- 2 hot green pepper
- 2 tablespoon tomato paste
- 250 g tomato
- 2 teaspoon salt
- 400ml fat coconut milk
- 120ml water
- 850 g canned chickpeas
- 3 tablespoon tahina
- 0.5 teaspoon sugar
- 200g chard
- 2 teaspoons garam masala
- 1 tablespoon lemon juice
- 50 g fresh mint
- 50 g fresh cilantro
- 1.5 teaspoons curry powder
- 0.5 teaspoon ground cinnamon
- 0.5 teaspoon grated nutmeg
- 0.25 teaspoon ground turmeric
- 0.5 teaspoon pepper
- 600 g rice
---
Add ingredients in steps, and cook them a bit before moving the the next step.
keep the heat rather low and be careful not to burn things.

- heat the oil and throw in the seed spices and curry leaves. keep the heat low
and be careful not to burn them. 
- add the chopped onions
- add the chopped ginger, garlic, green peppers
- add powder spices and tomato paste
- add diced tomatoes and their juice, plus salt
- add chickpeas, coconut milk, water and tahina
- cover and keep watching until cooked
- add the chard, cut. cook for more 5mn
- cut the fire. add lemon juice and fresh herbs, chopped